Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.00,0:00:02.54,style.default,,0,0,0,,2000 A.D., ANTARCTICA
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.09,0:00:06.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You're talking about Dr. Katsuragi's{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Super Solenoid Theory?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.05,0:00:09.38,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I must say,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}that theory is far too radical.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.47,0:00:12.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It's still very much a hypothesis.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.64,0:00:17.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But the S2 theory is the only explanation{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}for how that giant is being powered.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.48,0:00:20.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}There is no need to validate{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}what is already proven.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.35,0:00:23.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It exists right before us.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.57,0:00:25.69,style.default,,0,0,0,,-{\i1\c&Hffffff&}We must accept it.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}-Once all the data is in.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.78,0:00:30.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Scientists put far too much faith{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}in their beliefs.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.16,0:00:31.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You think they are dogmatic?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.91,0:00:34.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Their assumptions{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}are too deeply ingrained.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.54,0:00:37.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}These are people who are unable{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}to accurately perceive reality.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.79,0:00:41.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}And yet such people{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}seek the truth. How ironic.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.83,0:00:44.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}There is nothing noble about what they do.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:49.22,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The act of discovery brings them joy,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}and understanding leads to dominance.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.76,0:00:52.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}What they seek is self-gratification,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}nothing more.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.43,0:00:56.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Stop the surface luminescence!{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It's exceeding threshold values!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.39,0:01:00.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The DNA that was inserted into Adam{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}has undergone physical fusion!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.52,0:01:02.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}All the A.T. Fields are giving way!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.06,0:01:05.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}-The spear! Pull up the spear!{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}-No-go! Magnetic field unstable!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.69,0:01:06.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It's sinking in!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.90,0:01:09.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Limit the damage any way you can!{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Every bit counts!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.78,0:01:12.45,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Break up its component atoms{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}on the quark level! Hurry!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.87,0:01:16.79,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Initiate cooling cycle{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}the instant the Gates of Guf opens!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.87,0:01:18.95,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Incredible! It's walking!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.04,0:01:22.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Make it interfere with its own Anti-A.T.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Field! Even if only for a split second!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.38,0:01:25.96,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It's spreading its wings!{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It's reached the surface!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.27,0:01:45.98,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Like a cruel angel{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.23,0:01:52.86,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Become a legend, young boy{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.08,0:02:08.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}When a blue wind{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Knocks on the door to your heart{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.84,0:02:15.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You just gaze back at me{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}And smile oh so gently{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.76,0:02:23.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}So eager for something{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You touch so softly{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.85,0:02:30.86,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Those innocent eyes{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Know nothing of the fate that awaits{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:37.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But one day, you will realize{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}That upon your back{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.87,0:02:45.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You have wings{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You can fly to the faraway future{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:49.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The cruel angel's thesis{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.05,0:02:53.72,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}One day, you'll take off through a window{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.80,0:02:57.47,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}If your overflowing pathos{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.55,0:03:00.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Leads you to betray your memories{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.31,0:03:04.89,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Then embrace the heavens and shine bright{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.98,0:03:08.86,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Become legend, young boy{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.57,0:03:15.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Hello, I'm not home right now.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Leave a message after the beep.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.70,0:03:23.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,One last job to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.83,0:03:26.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's the same color as blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.63,0:03:31.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean,\Nthe deputy commander's been abducted?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.13,0:03:33.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,It happened two hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.13,0:03:37.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,His last confirmed location\Nwas in Ward Eight in the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.51,0:03:41.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's inside this facility!\NWere you guys at Intel asleep on the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.72,0:03:44.68,style.default,,0,0,0,,They had an inside man who was\Nleaking Intel and stirring up trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.06,0:03:46.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,He gave us the runaround.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.94,0:03:49.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,A man who could outwit Intel Section Two?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:50.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.23,0:03:54.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ryoji Kaji. We believe him to be\Nthe mastermind behind the disappearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.03,0:03:57.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,Which is why you came to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.61,0:03:59.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's helpful that you catch on so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.20,0:04:04.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,As colleagues, we hate having to suspect\Nour own chief of operations,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.62,0:04:06.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,but this is our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:10.54,style.default,,0,0,0,,Considering my history with him,\Nit's the logical step to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:13.46,style.default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation. Bring her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.46,0:04:17.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's been quite some time, Chairman Keel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.42,0:04:19.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is a rather rough welcome,\Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.14,0:04:22.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,Apologies for rude behavior\Nare not warranted here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.35,0:04:26.81,style.default,,0,0,0,,We needed to have an uninterrupted chat.\NIt was the logical step to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.14,0:04:31.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,You never change. My convenience\Nhas never been a concern for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:35.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,This matter requires immediate attention.\NIt couldn't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.86,0:04:37.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,Please understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.69,0:04:40.95,style.default,,0,0,0,,It must be, if you're appearing to me\Nas Seele rather than the Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.03,0:04:44.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,We have no intention\Nof creating a new god.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.28,0:04:47.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,We require your assistance,\NProfessor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.04,0:04:50.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}"Professor Fuyutsuki," is it?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.42,0:04:53.71,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Professor! Professor Fuyutsuki!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.30,0:04:57.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.42,0:05:00.01,style.default,,0,0,0,,Have any plans, sir?\NWant to grab a beer at Kamogawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.09,0:05:01.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.38,0:05:04.60,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ryoko and her friends say they'll come,\Nbut only if you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.93,0:05:07.60,style.default,,0,0,0,,The other professors say you ought\Nto join in every once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.10,0:05:09.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,All right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.02,0:05:13.81,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's good for you to go out for\Na drink every now and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.90,0:05:14.90,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.07,0:05:18.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,You're very talented,\Nbut you should give more thought
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.15,0:05:19.95,style.default,,0,0,0,,to cultivating relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.03,0:05:21.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'll take that to heart, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.61,0:05:25.58,style.default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Fuyutsuki,\Nthere's a student over in Bioengineering
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.66,0:05:27.95,style.default,,0,0,0,,who's put together a fascinating report.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:30.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,Do you know a student\Nby the name of Ikari?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.41,0:05:32.100,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ikari? No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.71,0:05:37.21,style.default,,0,0,0,,When I mentioned you and your work, Ikari\Nexpressed an interest in meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:40.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,This student will be in touch soon.\NBe accommodating, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.84,0:05:43.22,style.default,,0,0,0,,"Ikari," was it? Very well, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:44.80,style.default,,0,0,0,,METAPHYSICAL BIO, LAB NO.1\N(FUYUTSUKI)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.39,0:05:47.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,I've taken the liberty\Nof reading your report.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.39,0:05:50.43,style.default,,0,0,0,,There are a few points I'm not sold on,\Nbut it was a stimulating read.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.02,0:05:52.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.35,0:05:54.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,"Yui Ikari," was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:05:55.81,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.94,0:05:57.73,style.default,,0,0,0,,What are your plans after graduation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.82,0:06:01.65,style.default,,0,0,0,,Get a job in the private sector?\NOr take a position at a lab here, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.03,0:06:07.08,style.default,,0,0,0,,I haven't thought that far ahead yet.\NAnd isn't there also a third option?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:12.87,style.default,,0,0,0,,I've also thought about starting a family.\NAssuming I meet the right person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.04,0:06:17.25,style.default,,0,0,0,,AGAIN, IN 2015 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.63,0:06:19.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,By assimilating that S2 Drive...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.55,0:06:22.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,...it has attained absolute existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:24.38,style.default,,0,0,0,,Evangelion Unit 01...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.93,0:06:27.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,A manifested god is of no use to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.31,0:06:30.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,We mustn't create a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.56,0:06:34.14,style.default,,0,0,0,,Much less allow it\Nto fall into that man's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:37.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,Gendoh Ikari... Can this man be trusted?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.32,0:06:40.98,style.default,,0,0,0,,Gendoh Rokubungi?\NYes, I've heard the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:43.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}No, I've never personally met him.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:47.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But he is the sort of man{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}whose reputation precedes him.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.82,0:06:50.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}What? He's asking to be released{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}into {\c}{\i0}my{\i1\c&Hffffff&} custody?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:55.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}No, I'll come down.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}When would be a good time?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:06:58.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,I heard about you from a mutual friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.84,0:07:01.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to meet you for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.92,0:07:05.63,style.default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't expecting you to be\Nthe trashy sort who gets into bar brawls.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.22,0:07:09.01,style.default,,0,0,0,,He took a swing at me\Nbefore I could talk my way out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.30,0:07:13.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,Being liked makes me uncomfortable.\NI'm far more used to being an outcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.02,0:07:17.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,Well, your social skills\Nhave nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.85,0:07:22.36,style.default,,0,0,0,,Prof. Fuyutsuki, you seem to be exactly\Nthe sort of man I hoped you would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.65,0:07:27.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}My first impression was that he{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}was a thoroughly unpleasant man.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.24,0:07:32.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It was autumn at the time. This was back{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}when this country still had seasons.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.04,0:07:34.79,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Is that true?\N-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:37.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm in a relationship with Mr. Rokubungi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.100,0:07:41.50,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I could not hide my surprise{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}when I heard those words.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.13,0:07:45.38,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm surprised you have anything in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.84,0:07:50.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, Professor Fuyutsuki.\NHe's actually very charming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.72,0:07:51.93,style.default,,0,0,0,,No one knows it, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.02,style.default,,0,0,0,,Then perhaps ignorance really is bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.68,0:07:58.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,Was my introducing you an imposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.81,0:08:03.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,No. He's an interesting man, to be sure.\NBut I can't bring myself to like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.90,0:08:09.36,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}In my circles, it was widely thought that{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}he had fostered a relationship with Yui{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.45,0:08:12.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}to gain access to her talents{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}and the group she was associated with.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.83,0:08:17.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Later on, I heard rumors that{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}this group's name was "Seele."{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.46,0:08:18.83,style.default,,0,0,0,,ANTARCTICA, 2000 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:20.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The Second Impact.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.13,0:08:24.00,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}That tragedy struck in the final year{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}of the 20th Century.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.67,0:08:28.68,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}And the first year of the 21st Century{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}could only be described as Hell.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.01,0:08:31.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}There are no other words{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}to describe that year.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.59,0:08:32.43,style.default,,0,0,0,,2002 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.51,0:08:33.89,style.default,,0,0,0,,AICHI PREF., RUINS OF TOYOHASHI CITY
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.98,0:08:43.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,Another 30°C day today, they say.\NIt certainly is very hot here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.69,0:08:46.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,Not at all uncommon anymore.\NNot in Japan these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.44,0:08:51.45,style.default,,0,0,0,,Summer has lasted nearly an entire year.\NIt's really doing a number on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:53.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,Why not move to the ship up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.24,0:08:57.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,You mean the neighboring town?\NThat place constantly reeks of oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:08:59.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's too much for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.58,0:09:03.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,Even so, we didn't expect you to be\Nrunning a medical practice here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.33,0:09:05.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,It took considerable effort\Nto find you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.84,0:09:07.80,style.default,,0,0,0,,There's a shortage of doctors here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.09,0:09:10.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,I may just be playing the part,\Nbut I'm better than nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.89,0:09:14.68,style.default,,0,0,0,,Why go to Antarctica {\i1\c&Hffffff&}now?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.31,0:09:18.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's a formal investigation of\Nthe incident by the UN Security Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:20.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's a provisional group,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.73,0:09:23.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,but I think it will be a better way\Nto serve your fellow man
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.31,0:09:26.02,style.default,,0,0,0,,than being an unlicensed doctor\Nin the middle of nowhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.07,0:09:28.23,style.default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.61,0:09:30.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Former{\c}{\i0} professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.74,0:09:34.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,The space for who recommended me\Nis left blank. Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.66,0:09:36.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,ANTARCTICA, THAT SAME YEAR
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:41.71,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe that this\Nwas once a continent of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.29,0:09:43.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's utterly unrecognizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:45.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:48.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's you.\NI'm amazed you're still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.63,0:09:53.18,style.default,,0,0,0,,I heard you were on\Nthe Katsuragi Expedition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.43,0:09:56.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,As luck would have it, I had returned\Nto Japan the day beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.39,0:09:58.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,so I managed to avoid the tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.39,0:10:01.18,style.default,,0,0,0,,I see. Look, Rokubungi--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.27,0:10:03.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Professor,\Nbut I've changed my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.86,0:10:08.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,A postcard? Not a business card?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.27,0:10:09.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,WE'RE MARRIED!\NGENDOH AND YUI IKARI
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.40,0:10:12.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ikari... Gendoh {\i1\c&Hffffff&}Ikari?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.95,0:10:17.87,style.default,,0,0,0,,The missus insisted that I give this\Nto you, Professor. She's quite the fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.33,0:10:19.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm honored to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.41,0:10:23.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,So, how is Yui? She's not coming\Non this field expedition?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.33,0:10:28.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,She wanted to come with us,\Nbut we have a child now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.96,0:10:32.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,This organization you belong to.\NSeele, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.01,0:10:34.63,style.default,,0,0,0,,I've heard nothing but bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.93,0:10:38.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,I can't say I approve of the way\Nthey strong-arm the Security Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.68,0:10:40.43,style.default,,0,0,0,,As principled as ever, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.85,0:10:43.64,style.default,,0,0,0,,But these days, no organization\Nthat plays by the rules can survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.06,0:10:47.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,This official investigation\Nof the Second Impact...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.56,0:10:51.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,It would raise suspicions if it were\Ncomposed entirely of Seele members.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.74,0:10:55.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,That's why the rest of us\Nwere brought in, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:10:58.37,style.default,,0,0,0,,2015 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.45,0:11:00.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,NERV ISOLATION FACILITY NO.4
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.04,0:11:05.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I still don't like dark places.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Bad things always come back to me.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.08,0:11:06.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Who is she?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.42,0:11:09.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,The sole survivor\Nof the original expedition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.00,0:11:10.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,2002 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.96,0:11:12.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Misato Katsuragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.13,0:11:15.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,Katsuragi? The daughter\Nof {\i1\c&Hffffff&}Doctor {\c}{\i0}Katsuragi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.22,0:11:19.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes. She hasn't spoken a single word\Nin nearly two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.80,0:11:21.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,That poor girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:23.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,Whatever she saw,\Nit was bad enough to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.14,0:11:27.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,Mental trauma can take longer to heal\Nthan simple physical injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.40,0:11:29.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,Very true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.06,0:11:32.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,Releasing our findings\Nwill require careful attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.98,0:11:36.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,Alteration of atmospheric composition\Nconfined to a specific area.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.45,0:11:39.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,The total eradication of all life,\Nright down to the microorganisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.28,0:11:43.08,style.default,,0,0,0,,The remains of a vast subterranean\Nchamber beneath the epicenter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.58,0:11:45.46,style.default,,0,0,0,,And this giant of light...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.41,0:11:48.71,style.default,,0,0,0,,Everything about this incident\Nis a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.42,0:11:53.80,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Afterwards, the UN would officially report{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}that the Second Impact was caused by{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.88,0:11:55.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}the impact of a meteor of enormous mass.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:12:01.68,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}In my eyes, however,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}it was clear that this was a cover-up.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.43,0:12:07.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I could catch hints of Seele, and a man{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}called Keel, at work behind the scenes.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.60,0:12:10.98,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I wanted to learn more about{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}the dark truth behind this incident.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.86,0:12:15.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1\c&Hffffff&}Even if the name "Yui Ikari" popped up.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.37,0:12:24.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.87,0:12:26.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It certainly has.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.30,0:12:39.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,Why would you conceal\Nthe existence of the giant?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.80,0:12:44.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,Your group knew the Second Impact\Nwas coming, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.35,0:12:46.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,You knew it would happen that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.18,0:12:51.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,You mentioned you were lucky enough\Nto leave the day before the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.11,0:12:55.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,Was it also luck that you gathered all of\Nyour research material before you left?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.03,0:13:01.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,I thought all those had been incinerated.\NI'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.82,0:13:04.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,I've looked into your finances.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.54,0:13:07.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,I realize that it takes\Na lot of money to raise a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.83,0:13:10.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,but don't you think you have far more\Nthan any individual needs?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:12.83,style.default,,0,0,0,,Impressive as ever, Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.96,0:13:15.00,style.default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you should\Nchange fields to economics.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.59,0:13:17.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm going public with how your Seele group
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:20.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,and the Dead Sea Scrolls\Nare connected to the Second Impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:23.64,style.default,,0,0,0,,I refuse to let those responsible\Nget away with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.30,0:13:25.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:28.47,style.default,,0,0,0,,But before you do that,\Nthere's something I want you to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:32.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,We're certainly going down a long way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.15,0:13:35.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Does that worry you?\N-Somewhat, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.98,0:13:39.11,style.default,,0,0,0,,What on earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.19,0:13:41.99,style.default,,0,0,0,,A structure that was left behind\Nby someone who wasn't us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:44.45,style.default,,0,0,0,,Eighty-nine percent of it is buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.20,0:13:48.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,Then this was originally a perfectly\Nspherical underground space?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.37,0:13:52.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,Is it identical to the subterranean\Ncavern in Antarctica?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:54.96,style.default,,0,0,0,,The data is almost a perfect match.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.79,0:13:59.46,style.default,,0,0,0,,Are you people trying to\Nrecreate that tragedy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:02.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,Are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.47,0:14:06.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,See what we're doing\Nand judge for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.18,0:14:11.14,style.default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind's resources\Nare being poured into that installation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.52,0:14:19.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello, Professor Fuyutsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.03,0:14:21.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,Akagi? You're involved in this, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:25.03,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is the best place\Nto work out the basic theories
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.11,0:14:27.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,underpinning the biological computers\NI'm trying to create.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:31.45,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to call them the Magi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.54,0:14:34.58,style.default,,0,0,0,,Magi? The three wise men from the East?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.96,0:14:37.50,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Is that what you wanted to show me?\N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.46,0:14:41.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,This way, please.\NRitsuko, we'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.34,0:14:48.22,style.default,,0,0,0,,What on earth...\NSurely you didn't bring that giant here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.35,0:14:51.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,We Gehirn members refer to\Nthat object as "Adam."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.64,0:14:55.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the giant.\NIt's not the original.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.44,0:14:58.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,-So this is...\N-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.31,0:15:00.73,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is Eva, created by man from Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.44,0:15:02.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.74,0:15:07.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is the prototype of the Adam\NRebirth Project, also called Project-E.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.62,0:15:08.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,Eva-00.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.58,0:15:11.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,The prototype of a {\i1\c&Hffffff&}god?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.58,0:15:16.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,Fuyutsuki, will you join me in forging\Na new history for mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.09,0:15:22.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,2015 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.30,0:15:25.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,Um, Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:29.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry.\NLet's get Rei re-tested right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.72,0:15:31.93,style.default,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen Ms. Katsuragi around today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.01,0:15:33.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hadn't noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.56,0:15:35.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Katsuragi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.81,0:15:38.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yep, Misato Katsuragi!\NPleased to meet'cha!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.69,0:15:43.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Mother, I met a girl named{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Katsuragi the other day.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:46.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}People tend to give me a wide berth.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.65,0:15:49.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Whenever that happens, it drives home{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}how much weight your name carries.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.03,0:15:53.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But not her. She's totally at ease{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}around me for some reason.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.04,0:15:58.08,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I learned that she was the sole survivor{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}of that doomed expedition.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.46,0:16:00.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}She says she suffered from aphasia,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}unable to speak for a while,{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.00,0:16:04.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}but the way she goes on and on now,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}it's like she's making up for lost time.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.92,0:16:09.80,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Ritchan, I'm still spending{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}all my time underground here.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.18,0:16:12.22,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I'm really tired of the boxed{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}lunches they give us.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.76,0:16:14.89,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The Tokyo-3 project is underway topside{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:17.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}as part of the 2nd Capital{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Transfer Project.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.90,0:16:22.77,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Misato was away from school for a while,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}and when I made her tell me why,{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.86,0:16:24.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I couldn't believe it.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.57,0:16:26.99,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}She said she'd been in bed{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}with her boyfriend the whole time.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.40,0:16:30.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}They had just stayed there in bed{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}for a whole week.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.95,0:16:33.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I feel like I've learned about a side{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}to her I never knew existed.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.20,0:16:35.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}She introduced me to him today.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.08,0:16:39.79,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}He's handsome, but I'll never get used{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}to that carefree attitude of his.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:44.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Boys have never been your strong suit,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}have they, Ritchan?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.88,0:16:46.71,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Maybe being raised by a single mother...{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.38,0:16:50.72,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I'm sorry. I was never{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}a hands-on parent, was I?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.93,0:16:53.72,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I'm awful, I only act like a mother{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}when it takes no effort.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.35,0:16:57.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,Act like a mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:16:58.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,2003 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.48,0:16:59.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,HAKONE, LAKE ASHI LEVEE
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.39,0:17:02.36,style.default,,0,0,0,,Another day that's the same as the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.94,0:17:06.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you how much\NI miss autumn in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.98,0:17:11.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,According to the scenario set out\Nin Seele's Hidden Dead Sea Scrolls,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.74,0:17:14.58,style.default,,0,0,0,,the Third Impact will occur\Nsome ten years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.78,0:17:17.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,Two groups exist for the sole purpose\Nof preventing that final tragedy:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.12,0:17:19.87,style.default,,0,0,0,,Seele and Gehirn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.96,0:17:23.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's your views that I'm\Nin agreement with. Not Seele's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.54,0:17:29.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,Professor Fuyutsuki, breaking that seal\Nto the world is extremely dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.01,0:17:32.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,I've given all of my research to Ikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.97,0:17:35.18,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is beyond\Nwhat one single person can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.85,0:17:43.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention of repeating\Nmy previous behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:46.86,style.default,,0,0,0,,I've also received subtle warnings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.28,0:17:50.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,It looks like they could eliminate me\Nwith no trouble at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.57,0:17:52.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,The rest of us survivors, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:55.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's a simple thing to destroy people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.53,0:17:58.54,style.default,,0,0,0,,Even so, there's no reason for you\Nto be the test subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.50,0:18:01.71,style.default,,0,0,0,,I will ride along the currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.67,0:18:05.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm with Seele.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.09,0:18:07.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is also for Shinji.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.89,0:18:21.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,2004 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:23.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,HAKONE, UNDERGROUND\NTESTING FACILITY NO.2
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.69,0:18:25.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}LCL pressure, +0.2.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.02,0:18:27.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}No destrudo readings in transmitter.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.36,0:18:32.11,style.default,,0,0,0,,-What is this child doing here?\N-That's Director Ikari's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.74,0:18:36.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ikari, this isn't a daycare center.\NToday is an important day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.16,0:18:40.45,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Sorry, Professor Fuyutsuki.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I was the one who brought him.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.87,0:18:43.79,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yui? This is {\i1\c&Hffffff&}your{\c}{\i0} experiment today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.87,0:18:47.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}That's exactly why. I want him to see{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}that he has a bright future ahead of him.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.92,0:18:51.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Those were Ms. Yui's last words.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.76,0:18:55.43,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}That freak accident wiped her{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}from the face of the earth.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.55,0:18:58.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Just as I had hoped.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:01.64,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I'm a terrible woman, aren't I?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.89,0:19:06.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Ritchan, Director Ikari was{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}a changed man after that day.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.10,0:19:09.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,Where have you been all week?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.73,0:19:14.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,Grieve all you want, but remember that you\Nhave responsibilities beyond yourself now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.03,0:19:20.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm well aware. Fuyutsuki,\NI'm proposing a new project today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.83,0:19:22.100,style.default,,0,0,0,,I've already submitted it\Nto Chairman Keel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:24.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,Surely you don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.96,0:19:28.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,I do. The path to attain godhood,\Nwhich no one has ever achieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.25,0:19:31.00,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Human Instrumentality Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.38,0:19:32.21,style.default,,0,0,0,,2008 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:38.89,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Mother, congratulations on completing{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}the basic theories for the Magi.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.10,0:19:42.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I've been informally accepted into Gehirn.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.60,0:19:45.43,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I'm set to work as part of{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Project-E starting next month.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.82,0:19:51.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.65,0:19:57.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ritsuko Akagi, Technology\NDevelopment Department. My ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.78,0:20:01.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,I heard that the Command Center has\Nbeen framed out, so I came to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.83,0:20:02.99,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's a real maze here, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:07.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Director is there\Nwith Dr. Akagi right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.75,0:20:12.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Are you sure?\N-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.71,0:20:14.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,I have no regrets about my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.59,0:20:17.47,style.default,,0,0,0,,Liar. You can't let go of Ms. Yui.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.76,0:20:21.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,But I can live with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.81,0:20:31.69,style.default,,0,0,0,,2010 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.86,0:20:33.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}GEO-FRONT ARTIFICIAL CANOPY
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.27,0:20:35.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}VENTRAL POINT DEFENSE EMPLACEMENT NO.2\N(PLANNED SITE)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:38.86,style.default,,0,0,0,,That's Gehirn HQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.99,0:20:44.45,style.default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Director.\NYou have your son with you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.08,0:20:47.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I thought you had a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.79,0:20:51.63,style.default,,0,0,0,,This isn't Shinji.\NI'm looking after a friend's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.17,0:20:53.63,style.default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Rei Ayanami.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.21,0:20:55.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,Hi there, Rei.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.55,0:20:59.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}She reminds me of someone...{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.68,0:21:01.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Ms. Yui?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.14,0:21:06.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,All files pertaining to Rei Ayanami\Nhave been deleted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:09.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,She's a blank slate. What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.44,0:21:11.56,style.default,,0,0,0,,SUPERCOMPUTER MAGI SYSTEM\NCOMPLETED
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.90,0:21:15.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,Magus Casper, Magus Balthasar,\Nand Magus Melchior.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.07,0:21:20.65,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Magi are the three sides of me.\NMe as a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.82,0:21:24.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,Me as a mother. Me as a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.87,0:21:26.99,style.default,,0,0,0,,Those three sides are constantly\Nvying for control.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:28.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,Three of you, Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.46,0:21:31.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,All that's left is to power it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.63,0:21:37.00,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm leaving early today.\NMisato is coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.13,0:21:39.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. She's also\Njoined Gehirn, hasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.30,0:21:41.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,In Germany, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.80,0:21:43.89,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she works at the Third Branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.05,0:21:47.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,-A long-distance relationship, then?\N-She says they broke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.77,0:21:50.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh? That's too bad.\NThey seemed like the perfect couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.02,0:21:53.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,Men and women are hard to figure out.\NThere's no logic to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.69,0:21:57.23,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ever the aloof ice queen, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.73,0:22:00.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,Careful, happiness is going\Nto pass you by.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.24,0:22:03.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,I have even more trouble with\Nhow to define happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.32,0:22:06.99,style.default,,0,0,0,,I should go. It's been forever\Nsince I went out for a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.33,0:22:09.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Good work today.\N-You, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.34,0:22:24.72,style.default,,0,0,0,,Can I help you, Rei?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.55,0:22:26.60,style.default,,0,0,0,,I got lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.05,0:22:30.43,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? Well, do you want me\Nto show you the way out?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.02,0:22:33.02,style.default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.10,0:22:35.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,But you can't find your way out\Nby yourself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.48,0:22:37.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,I don't need your help, you hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.19,0:22:40.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.28,0:22:42.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,I can find my own way out,\Nso leave me alone, you hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.70,0:22:46.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,Calling someone a hag is very rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.78,0:22:48.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,But you are one, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.99,0:22:52.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,You're making me angry.\NYou need a scolding from Director Ikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.66,0:22:56.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,-He's the one who says that about you.\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}-What?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.42,0:23:00.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,Things like, "That old hag is such a nag."\NOr, "I don't need that hag anymore."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.84,0:23:03.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,"That hag is such a nag."\N"I don't need that hag anymore."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.47,0:23:09.60,style.default,,0,0,0,,"I don't need that hag anymore."\NHe's the one who says that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.89,0:23:11.64,style.default,,0,0,0,,"I don't need that hag anymore."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.11,0:23:22.99,style.default,,0,0,0,,Even if you die, there will be another\Nto take your place, Rei...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.15,0:23:25.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,Just like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.71,0:23:38.25,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}On that day, the Human Instrumentality{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Project, chaired by Keel Lorenz,{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.38,0:23:41.05,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}dissolved Gehirn,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}its research organization.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.55,0:23:43.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The Special Agency Nerv was founded{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.59,0:23:45.80,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}as the execution organization{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}for all of its projects.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.13,0:23:49.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}And then we were all{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}transferred over to Nerv.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.05,0:23:51.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Except for Dr. Akagi,{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.39,0:23:55.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}the key figure behind the development{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}of the Magi System.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.39,0:23:56.23,style.default,,0,0,0,,2015 A.D.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.77,0:23:59.69,style.default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.15,0:24:07.36,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Oh, it's you.\N-It's been a while, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.49,0:24:11.08,style.default,,0,0,0,,The guard outside is getting\Na little shut-eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.28,0:24:13.91,style.default,,0,0,0,,Doing this will mean your neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.50,0:24:16.50,style.default,,0,0,0,,I just want to get closer to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.25,0:24:18.46,style.default,,0,0,0,,The truth inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.100,0:24:21.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,Plus, they're about to figure out\Nthat I was the one
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.25,0:24:23.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,who snuck the Adam sample\Nto the Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.59,0:24:26.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,If I don't take steps to endear myself,\Nthings could get hairy for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.22,0:24:28.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,From various quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.18,0:24:34.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.89,0:24:39.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,-I'm free to go?\N-Yes. The issue has been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.19,0:24:43.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.11,0:24:45.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,-And him?\N-Unknown, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.75,0:25:01.83,style.default,,0,0,0,,Hi. What took you so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.93,0:25:15.01,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.04,0:25:38.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,MESSAGE
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.50,0:25:48.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,PLAY MESSAGES
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.76,0:25:56.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Hi, Katsuragi. It's me.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.35,0:26:01.98,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}By the time you get this message,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I've probably made life difficult for you.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.69,0:26:06.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Sorry about that.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}And apologize to Ritchan for me, okay?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.94,0:26:11.03,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I shouldn't be asking favors,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}but I've been growing some flowers.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.57,0:26:14.03,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}If you could water them for me,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I'd appreciate it.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.20,0:26:16.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Shinji knows where they are.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.16,0:26:23.08,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Katsuragi, the truth is with you.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Keep going and don't look back.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.04,0:26:27.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}If I see you again...{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.38,0:26:30.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I'll say the words that I couldn't{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}say to you eight years ago.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.59,0:26:32.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Bye.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.13,0:26:35.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Message left at 12:02 p.m.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.85,0:26:39.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,You idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.35,0:26:44.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,You're such an idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.00,0:27:11.00,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}All I could do was hide from Misato.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.05,0:27:16.05,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I knew there was nothing I could do.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Nothing I could say.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.93,0:27:19.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I was just a child.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.22,0:27:22.18,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}TO BE CONTINUED
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.77,0:28:53.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,NEXT EPISODE
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.32,0:28:57.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Asuka is in a mental downward spiral{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}over being one-upped by Shinji.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.99,0:28:59.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Wasted energy in the form of impatience{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.74,0:29:01.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}only results in exhaustion{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}and frustration.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.16,0:29:04.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}And then a mental attack{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}unleashed by an Angel{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.28,0:29:06.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}delivers the final blow to her heart.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.54,0:29:08.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Asuka loses her only means{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}of bouncing back.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.50,0:29:11.83,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The harshness of reality{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}wears down everyone's hearts.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.21,0:29:15.38,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Shinji has no words{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}with which to console her.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.05,0:29:18.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Next episode, "Staying Human".{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.76,0:29:25.01,style.default,,0,0,0,,Translator: Dan Kanemitsu\NSubtitle Editor: David Fleming
